title: Print, Portrait of a Man, Plate 6, from the series Raccolta Di Teste I, ca. 1757
title_raw: Portrait of a Man, Plate 6, from the series Raccolta Di Teste I
provenance:
From the Collection of Eleanor and Sarah Hewitt, purchased in Paris, August 1905.
Ex-collection M. Charles Toché (1851-1916)
Notations of some in the group contain "Bossi-Beyerlen" codes, a system of notes, inventory numbers and prices found only in the Tiepolo drawings sold in the Bossi-Beyerlen sale in Stuttgart in 1882. These inscriptions have been identified as by Dominico Tiepolo. 
This evidence suggests that the Hewitt Album is Domenico's own collection of the family etchings.
description: Man in a turban with full beard, full face, looking right

tombstone.epitaph:
Print, Portrait of a Man, Plate 6, from the series Raccolta Di Teste I, ca. 1757. Etching on white laid paper. 
1931-67-106-2.
